Apple's latest <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/apple-pay/">Apple Pay</a> promotion is offering Apple users in the U.S. a discount on flowers ahead of Valentine's Day. Customers can get &#36;20 off of a 1-800-Flowers purchase of &#36;49.99 or more when using &zwnj;Apple Pay&zwnj;.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2026/01/apple-pay-promo-flowers.jpg" alt="" width="1472" height="828" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1034243" /><br/>
The discount is available from now until February 12, and it is available when ordering flowers <a href="https://www.1800flowers.com/apple-pay">from the 1-800-Flowers website</a> or app. To get the deal, use &zwnj;Apple Pay&zwnj; when checking out, and enter the promo code APPLEPAY.<br/>
<br/>
1-800-Flowers is able to provide flower deliveries across the United States, with bouquet options varying by location.<div class="linkback">Tag: <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/apple-pay-promo/">Apple Pay Promo</a></div><br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2026/01/28/apple-pay-promo-valentine-flowers/">Apple Pay Promo Offers Discount on Valentine&#039;s Day Flowers</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/apple-pay-promo-offers-discount-on-valentines-day-flowers.2476794/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>